<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[128,654,1611,1754]" lastBlockId="26.[701,1227,211,352]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
This group includes a single species, from 
<collectingRegion box="[128,216,1641,1665]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Florida</collectingRegion>
, that may represent the sister group of all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Atkinson" authorityYear="1886" box="[259,430,1671,1695]" class="Arachnida" family="Cyrtaucheniidae" genus="Myrmekiaphila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[259,430,1671,1695]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Myrmekiaphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Males lack the expanded ledge on the palpal tibia (fig. 102) and show only vague traces of a single embolar tooth (on the distal, rather than proximal, edge of the embolus). Alternatively, these features could represent a derived condition, thus representing a loss rather than a plesiomorphy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
